93 giraffe died during the 2022 drought. The deaths occurred mostly outside ANP (91.40%) and were widespread within the dispersal area (Figure 10). 70.97% (n=66) were adults, 29.03% (n=27) young. 31 (33.33%) were females, 13 (13.98%) were males, while majority (52.69%; n=49) were unsexed (Table 2).
